title: Ferry Inn built daughter Queen Victoria by Edwin Lutyen
text: Princess Louise's romantic hideaway: The stunning home built for the daughter of Queen Victoria by the architect she 'secretly loved' Dr Brown bought the Ferry Inn a decade ago and spent £1.5 million restoring Grade I listed property was built for Queen Victoria’s daughter Princess Louise It was designed by Sir Edwin Lutyens, architect of the Cenotaph in Whitehall Married princess Louise, Victoria’s fourth daughter, is said to have been in love with Lutyens, who was just 27 when he built the house for her in 1896
